grass (5.0.3-2) unstable; urgency=low

  The "Check twice before releasing" release.

  (Federico)

  * Changes to debian/rules as suggested by Markus Neteler:
    + added dh_shlibdeps to generate dependencies
    + --without-blas, --without-lapack: both not needed because the
      module using them was never finished (also removed the Build-deps)
    + --without-dbm: dbm is not used in grass, it is a fake dependency
      (also removed gdbm patch)
    + Markus said:
    
      AFAIK there is no GRASS module which uses that.
      The only existing module was written by me and never submitted, as
      the lapack/blas implementation is still incomplete (someone who left
      the project did it for me). So it's to come thenext ten years...
    
      It's a nice unrequired dependency, nearly as useless as dbm at time
      and for the foreseeable future.

  * manpages are still lost somewhere in time during the install step.
    
 -- Federico Di Gregorio <fog@initd.org>  Thu, 15 Jan 2004 16:59:33 +0100
  
grass (5.0.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

    The "Release soon" release (Francesco P. Lovergine).

    - New upstream version (closes: #208449, #214496).
    - Copyright file cleaned of outdated (and bad) licenses.
    - Policy bumped to 3.6.1.
    - Added me as co-maintainer.
    - Added dpatch support.
    	+ debian/rules
        + debian/control
      	Patches currently applied:
      		+ configure.in (run autoconf2.13 for any modification!!)
                    	o use gdbm_compat dbm compatibility funcs
                        o avoid freetype.h check
                + freetype
                        o freetype.h should not be included as is, see
                          freetype/freetype.h

    - Changed config.status in configure-stamp to follow normal
      conventions. Other targets changed as consequence.
      	+ debian/control
    - CVS-enabled debian/ dir
    - Changed download site. Added citation of GPL license copy
      in /usr/share/common-licenses (policy).
      	+ debian/copyright
    - Include dir for freetype2 is /usr/include/freetype2/freetype
    	+ debian/rules
    - Added build-deps in control file:
    	+ libgdbm-dev for --with-dbm
    	+ libreadline4-dev for --with-readline
    	+ xlibmesa-glu-dev for --with-opengl
    	+ libfreetype6-dev for --with-freetype
        + bison
        + flex
        + libncurses5-dev
    - Removed autoconf build-dep in control file.
    - Fixed debian/fixscripts.sh
    - Added autotools-dev build-dep and updating of config.guess and
      config.guess in rules file.

 -- Francesco Paolo Lovergine <frankie@debian.org>  Mon,  5 Jan 2004 19:24:22 +0100

grass (5.0.2-1) unstable; urgency=low
  
  * New upstream version (Closes: #179537).
  * Added "proj" to suggestions (Closes: #200403).
  * Updated Build-depends (Closes: #189874).
  * Fixed some more interpreter-not-absolute lintian errors.
  * Documentation splitted into grass-doc package (Closes: #159377)
  * Updated standards to 3.6.0.
  * Updated build scripts to DH_COMPAT=4.
  * Build against tcl/tk 8.4 (Closes: #206844).
  * Patches configure.in to look for libgdbm_compat (Closes: #203834).

